&lt;h3&gt;Associate, Containment&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Venue Infrastructure (VNI) team plays a critical role in delivering Games-specific temporary infrastructure for competition and non-competition venues to ensure that they are functional, innovative, and fully accessible for the Olympic and Paralympic Games. As part of the larger Sport and Games Delivery group, the VNI team ensures that all venues are designed, developed, and delivered with the highest standards for functionality, sustainability, and inclusion.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Manager, Containment, this role will be responsible with helping support and share this workload with Managers to be able to achieve this milestone. In order to maintain the pace of future TVDB submittals, this will require similar additional roles as the required level of detail and number of venues increases.  &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate, Containment will coordinate publication of design packages through project milestones of stakeholder review, procurement, and permitting. Collaboration across the LA28 organization will be done to meet cost, scheduling and quality targets. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Collaborate with internal teams on containment technical design and development. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:1080,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Follow technical engineering design guides

