&lt;h2&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Associate, Games Data, Demand Model, and Code Set&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position &lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate, Games Data, Demand Model, and Code Set, will play a key role in developing LA28’s data and analysis capability as part of the Planning and Programs team. This role will support the development of LA28’s Games Demand Model, the single source of truth containing the latest demand data and assumptions for LA28, ensuring all functional areas are planning their operations from the same baseline. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; This position will be leading the day-to-day activities around the development and maintenance of the Games Demand Model and its components: creation and maintenance of key data sets, support to the data owners and stewards across LA28 to maintain data accuracy and completeness, support the ETL (extract, transform and load) process and the development of business intelligence insights through various reports and ad-hoc analysis. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; The ideal candidate will be proactive, possess strong communication abilities and have experience as a data analyst. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will report directly into the Games Data and Analysis Director and work closely with a variety of data owners and stewards across LA28’s functional areas. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  &lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  &lt;strong&gt;Games Demand Model&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead the day-to-day maintenance of the Games Demand Model, ensuring that all LA28 functional areas and external partners make use of the latest demand data and assumptions &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create, store, maintain, archive and dispose of Games Demand Model datasets and code sets in compliance with legal and regulatory requirements &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
